Sentencas: The suggestion has been made in the literature that solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) operated with syngas as fuel may be viable in certain gas ratio regimes.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cell with NiCo-YSZ cermet anode for oxidation of CO/H2 fuel mixtures

Sentencas: We have explored this hypothesis with a promising bimetallic anode material.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cell with NiCo-YSZ cermet anode for oxidation of CO/H2 fuel mixtures

Sentencas: SOFCs with Ni0.7Co0.3-YSZ cermet anodes were operated with CO/H-2 mixtures in the full concentration range.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cell with NiCo-YSZ cermet anode for oxidation of CO/H2 fuel mixtures

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy and voltammetry measurements were employed to measure the exchange current density (i(0)) values of each fuel mixture.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cell with NiCo-YSZ cermet anode for oxidation of CO/H2 fuel mixtures

Sentencas: The fuel mixtures of CO/H-2 ratios corresponding to the range 20/80 and 30/70 were found to have i(0) values larger than that of pure H-2 with the same cell.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cell with NiCo-YSZ cermet anode for oxidation of CO/H2 fuel mixtures

Sentencas: For these two fuel ratios, an improvement of 5-8 times, respectively, in the exchange current density has been observed.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cell with NiCo-YSZ cermet anode for oxidation of CO/H2 fuel mixtures

Sentencas: Higher CO/H-2 fuel ratios in the range of 60/40-80/20 produced i(0) values lower than H-2, as carbon poisoning is operational in this region.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cell with NiCo-YSZ cermet anode for oxidation of CO/H2 fuel mixtures

Sentencas: Continuous running of a cell with fuel ratio 25/75 CO/H-2 for 7 days produced i(0) values above the values for pure H-2 as has been recently suggested.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cell with NiCo-YSZ cermet anode for oxidation of CO/H2 fuel mixtures
